@startuml
title Platform Version Structure (SemVer Compatibility Universe)
top to bottom direction

' =========================
' DARK MODE REVIEW THEME
' =========================

skinparam backgroundColor #121417
skinparam shadowing false
skinparam defaultFontName JetBrains Mono
skinparam defaultFontColor #f3f5f7
skinparam linetype polyline
skinparam nodesep 70
skinparam ranksep 80

skinparam rectangle {
  BackgroundColor #24303b
  BorderColor #7a8a9b
  FontColor #ffffff
  RoundCorner 10
}

skinparam package {
  BackgroundColor #1b2128
  BorderColor #5f6a75
  FontColor #ffffff
}

skinparam note {
  BackgroundColor #2a3138
  BorderColor #8b98a6
  FontColor #f3f5f7
}

skinparam ArrowColor #79b8ff
skinparam ArrowFontColor #f3f5f7

package "Compatibility Universe: MAJOR = 1" #1f2b36 {

  rectangle "Platform Release v1.0.0" as PlatformV1 {

    rectangle "Runtime Artifacts" as Runtime {
      rectangle "core_engine binary" as CE
      rectangle "core_mod.dll" as CM
    }

    rectangle "Contract Root (Compile-Time)" as Contracts {
      rectangle "core_engine_contract v1.0.0" as CEC
      rectangle "core_mod_contract v1.0.0" as CMC
    }
  }

  rectangle "Mod Versions Targeting v1.0.0" as ModsV1 {
    rectangle "alice/cool_magic v1.2.0" as M1
    rectangle "bob/physics_plus v2.3.1" as M2
  }
}

package "Separate Universe: MAJOR = 2 (future)" #2c2438 {
  rectangle "Any v2.x platform release" as PlatformV2
}

CEC --> CMC : contract root layering
M1 -up-> CMC : binds to contract root
M2 -up-> CMC : binds to contract root

M1 -up-> CM : runtime implementation target
M2 -up-> CM : runtime implementation target

M1 -[norank,#c87878,dashed]-> PlatformV2 : forbidden cross-major compatibility
M2 -[norank,#c87878,dashed]-> PlatformV2 : forbidden cross-major compatibility

M1 -[hidden]- M2

note right of PlatformV1
SemVer Rules:
- Platform MAJOR defines compatibility universe
- No mutation after release
- Mods bind to exactly one platform version
- New MAJOR creates a separate universe
end note

@enduml
